---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TravelList from '../components/TravelList.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Underrated Atlas" description="An evolving list of underrated places — originally crowd-sourced from Farcaster in 2023 and added to since.">
  <article>
    <h1>Underrated Atlas</h1>
    <p>As of 2023, I've visited 47 countries. My hope is to make it to 100 before I kick the bucket. One thing that becomes obvious the more you travel is that it's usually the places outside the obvious city capitals or postcard panoramas that teach you the most about a region. This is especially true as most major cities start to blur together. These are often the places most likely to teach you about how local people live, eat, shop, work, and learn. They are the most likely to feel magical.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">The list below was originally compiled from the Farcaster community in 2023, and I've added to it since then based on recs from travel aficionado friends.</p>
    <TravelList />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
